A R E S O L U T I O N
To urge Ohioans to safely store and secure firearms. 1
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE STATE OF
OHIO:
WHEREAS, The Second Amendment to the United States 2
Constitution protects the individual right to keep and bear 3
arms; and 4
WHEREAS, With this right comes the responsibility to ensure 5
that firearms are stored and secured in a manner that prevents 6
unauthorized access and reduces the risk of accidental injury or 7
death; and 8
WHEREAS, Unintentional shootings, particularly those 9
involving children, are a tragic and preventable public health 10
issue; and 11
WHEREAS, Safe storage practices, such as using gun safes, 12
lock boxes, and trigger locks, and storing ammunition 13
separately, can significantly reduce the risk of unintentional 14
shootings and firearm theft; and 15
WHEREAS, Public education and awareness about the 16

